CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, November 16, 1946, pg. 15, reads: "[Ilegible]...THE CHOW - Enthusiastic boys who attended the Invasion Day program held last Saturday and Sunday at the Centre Avenue branch YMCA cart some of the groceries just before meal time.  Beds to accommodate the 118 youngsters were set up in gym of the 'Y.'  Seventy-five cots were loaned by the Red Cross and twenty-five from the Downtown 'Y.'  Left to right: David Peterson, William Willingham, William Peterson, Donell Gloster and Theodore Williams. - Harris photo."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of David Peterson, William Willingham, William Peterson, Donell Gloster, and Theodore Williams carrying sacks of potatoes and large soup pot, on sidewalk, Centre Avenue, Hill District
